In a phone call, President Obama and Chancellor Merkel discussed several foreign policy issues, including Iran and Syria. They both expressed hope that Iran would address concerns about its nuclear program during the upcoming P5+1 talks. If Iran remained unresponsive, they agreed to increase pressure through sanctions and other measures. They also shared concern about the Assad government in Syria not complying with the Kofi Annan agreement and engaging in brutality against its own people. They emphasized the need for the UN Security Council to take stronger action. President Obama mentioned his anticipation of hosting Chancellor Merkel at Camp David for the G-8 Summit and continuing their consultations on important issues.